The hexahedron of vertices
(0,0,0)       (NBINHX,0,0)      (NBINHX,NBINHY,0)      (0,NBINHY,0)
(0,0,NBINHZ)  (NBINHX,0,NBINHZ) (NBINHX,NBINHY,NBINHZ) (0,NBINHY,NBINHZ)
is subdivided into NBINHX * NBINHY * NBINHZ hexahedra.

Example:
HEXAHEDRON11; I; 11; 5; 6; 7;
Define 5*6*7=210 equal regular hexahedra.
